text: Robert Holmes was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons in 1653. Holmes was a Justice of the Peace of Netherton, Gloucestershire in 1649. James Bennet The History of Tewkesbury In 1653, he was elected Member of Parliament for Gloucestershire in the Barebones Parliament. Holmes and married Elizabeth Kyrle, daughter of Francis Kyrle.John Burke A genealogical and heraldic history of the commoners of Great Britain, Volume 3 ==References== Category:Year of birth missing Category:Year of death missing Category:English MPs 1653 (Barebones) Category:Politicians from Gloucestershire
